====Noun====
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|linguistics}} A higher-pitched or stronger ([[loud]]er orÂ [[long]]er) [[articulation]] of a particular [[syllable]] of a word or phrase in order to [[distinguish]] it from the others or to [[emphasize]] it.
#: {{syn|en|stress}}
#: {{hypo|en|stress|stress accent|pitch|pitch accent}}
#: {{ux|en|In the word "careful", the '''accent''' is placed on the first syllable.}}
# {{lb|en|figuratively}} Emphasis or importance in general.
#: {{ux|en|At this hotel, the '''accent''' is on luxury.}}
# {{lb|en|orthography}} A [[mark]] or [[character]] used in writing, in order to indicate the place of the [[spoken]] accent, or to indicate the nature or quality of the vowel marked.
#: {{ux|en|The name CÃ©zanne is written with an acute '''accent'''.}}
# {{senseid|en|modulation of the voice}} [[modulation|Modulation]] of the voice in speaking; the manner of speaking or pronouncing; a peculiar or characteristic modification of the voice, expressing emotion; [[tone]].
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare King Lear|II|ii|text=I know, sir, I am no flatterer: he that beguiled you in a plain '''accent''' was a plain knave; which for my part I will not be, though I should win your displeasure to entreat me to 't.}}
#* '''1696''', [[w: Matthew Prior|Matthew Prior]], "From Celia to Damon", in ''Poems on Several Occasions''
#*: The tender '''Accent''' of a Woman's Cry / Will pass unheard, will unregarded die;
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1815|author={{w|Jane Austen}}|title={{w|Emma}}|volume=I| section=chapter 15| passage=And he repeated her words with such assurance of '''accent''', such boastful pretence of amazement, that she could not help replying with quickness â€¦}}
# {{lb|en|linguistics|sociolinguistics}} The distinctive manner of [[pronouncing]] a language associated with a particular region, social group, etc., whether of a native speaker or a foreign speaker; the [[phonetic]] and [[phonological]] aspects of a [[dialect]].
#: {{ux|en|a foreign '''accent''''' &nbsp; ''an American, British or Australian '''accent'''}}
#: {{ux|en|a broad Irish '''accent'''}}
#: {{ux|en|a hint of a German '''accent'''}}
# {{lb|en|linguistics|sign languages}} A distinctive manner of [[producing]] a [[sign language]], such as someone who does not normally use a certain sign language might have when using it.
#*{{quote-text|en|year=2008|author=Jeremy Linn Brunson|title=The Practice and Organization of Sign Language| page=76| passage=I believe I still retain some of my hearing '''accent''' when I use American Sign Language.}}
#* <!-- good example even if not durable -->'''2015''' December 3, ''[./http://www.pri.org/stories/2015-12-03/philadelphia-accent-sign-language There's a distinctly Philadelphia '''accent''' in American Sign Language]''
# A [[word]]; a significant [[tone]] or [[sound]].
#* {{RQ:Corelli Sorrows of Satan|page=20
|text=I heard my landlady's '''accents''' attuned to nervous civility, mingling with the mellow tones of a deep masculine voice,
}}
# {{lb|en|usually|plural only}} Expressions in general; [[speech]].
#* {{RQ:Dryden Virgil|Pastoral 3|text=Winds! on your wings to Heaven her '''accents''' bear, / Such words as Heaven alone is fit to hear.}}
# {{lb|en|prosody|poetry}} Stress laid on certain syllables of a [[verse]].
# {{lb|en|music}} A regularly [[recur]]ring [[stress]] upon the tone to mark the beginning, and, more feebly, the third part of the [[measure]].
# {{lb|en|music}} A special [[emphasis]] of a tone, even in the weaker part of the measure.
# {{lb|en|music}} A mark used to represent this special emphasis.[[File:Notation accents.png|thumb|The third and fourth symbols are '''accents''' (marks used to represent special emphasis in music).]]
# {{lb|en|music}} The rhythmical accent, which marks [[phrase]]s and [[section]]s of a [[period]].
# {{lb|en|mathematics}} A [[prime]] symbol.
# Emphasis laid on a part of an [[artistic]] design or [[composition]]; an emphasized detail, in particular a detail in sharp [[contrast]] to its surroundings.
# A very small [[gemstone]] set into a [[piece]] of [[jewellery]].
# {{lb|en|archaic}} [[utterance|Utterance]].

=====Usage notes=====
The word "accent" is often used specifically to refer to manners of speech that differ significantly from the local standard or one's personal speech.

