===Etymology===
From pre-Indo-European {{m|ine-pro||*mÃ©hâ‚‚ters}}.

In older literature usually reconstructed de-laryngealized as {{m|ine-pro||*mÄtÄ“r}} and explained as a combination of a nursery word {{m|ine-pro||*ma|mother}} and the agentive suffix {{m|ine-pro|*-tá¸—r|*-tÄ“r}}. However, Balto-Slavic forms have acute accent and require a root laryngeal and a short vowel, reflecting *mÃ©hâ‚‚- (as opposed to *má¸—hâ‚‚- which would have yielded a circumflexed vowel). Also, no trace of a lengthened grade in the root can be found: in no language did Eichner's law operate (which predicts non-coloration of the *Ä“ in *má¸—hâ‚‚-tr).

