====Conjugation====
{{la-conj|irreg.sigmpasv|faciÅ}}
{{m|la|fÄ“ced|FÄ“ced}} is an early form of {{m|la|fÄ“cit}}.

;Passive: If one were to follow the Proto-Italic verb {{m|itc-pro|*fakiÅ|*fakiÅ, *fakiesi}}, the passive would be ''facior'', ''facÄ«'' in the present. However, these forms are not attested before or during the Classical period.

====Usage notes====
''Facere'' renders a sense of doing or making with respect to a specific instance of so doing or making; for more continuative senses of doing or making, compare {{l|la|ago}}, {{l|la|agito}} and {{l|la|gero}}. In [[Late Latin|Late]] and [[Medieval Latin]] the verb was used with infinitives to form causative constructions (e.g. cf. {{m|en|fieri facias}}), which are a calque from (Proto-)Romance considered inappropriate in [[Classical Latin]].

