#* '''1744''', {{w|Georg Friedrich HÃ¤ndel}}, ''[[:w:Hercules (Handel)|Hercules]]'', act 2, scene 8
#*: Love and Hymen, hand in hand, / Come, restore the nuptial band! / And sincere delights prepare / To crown the hero and the '''fair'''.
#* {{RQ:Fielding Tom Jones|passage=Here Jones, having ordered a servant to show a room above stairs, was ascending, when the dishevelled '''fair''', hastily following, was laid hold on by the master of the house, who cried, â€œHeyday, where is that beggar wench going? Stay below stairs, I desire you.â€}}
